{
    "info": {
        "name": "VaxTrack — Operational Manager Module",
        "_postman_id": "vaxtrack-om-v1-2026",
        "description": "Complete Operational Manager API collection for VaxTrack. Login first (folder 0) to auto-capture {{omToken}}. Set {{baseUrl}} = http://localhost:5000.\n\n## End-to-end state flow (2026 refactor)\n1. OM Dispatch — POST /api/logistics/assign on a RATE_FIXED enquiry → Logistics.assignmentStatus = IN_PROGRESS; Enquiry.status = IN_PROGRESS (SLA cron only resets legacy ASSIGNED selector slots).\n2. Driver trip — Submitting a trip does NOT set Enquiry to COMPLETED; only Trip records (and optional PATCH /api/execution/:id/review for the trip) apply.\n3. Munshi packing — POST /api/munshi/packing/:assignmentId → Packing SUBMITTED, Logistics assignmentStatus COMPLETED until OM packing decision.\n4. OM Approve packing (terminal) — POST .../assignments/:assignmentId/approve → Packing APPROVED, Logistics APPROVED, Enquiry.status = COMPLETED.\n\n## Packing lifecycle\n1. Munshi submits → SUBMITTED + assignment COMPLETED\n2. OM reject (optional) → REJECTED + omRemark\n3. Munshi resubmit → SUBMITTED + assignment COMPLETED\n4. OM approve → APPROVED + Enquiry COMPLETED\n\n## Variables (cross-collection)\nPaste into this collection before dispatch: {{enquiryId}} (Mongo _id from Field Owner create response), {{companyId}}, {{munshiId}}, {{driverId}} from master-data dropdowns. POST Assign Logistics saves {{assignmentId}} automatically.",
        "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
    },
    "variable": [
        {
            "key": "baseUrl",
            "value": "http://localhost:5000",
            "type": "string"
        },
        {
            "key": "omToken",
            "value": "",
            "type": "string"
        },
        {
            "key": "assignmentId",
            "value": "",
            "type": "string"
        },
        {
            "key": "enquiryId",
            "value": "",
            "type": "string"
        },
        {
            "key": "driverId",
            "value": "",
            "type": "string"
        },
        {
            "key": "munshiId",
            "value": "",
            "type": "string"
        },
        {
            "key": "vehicleId",
            "value": "",
            "type": "string"
        },
        {
            "key": "companyId",
            "value": "",
            "type": "string"
        }
    ],
    "item": [
        {
            "name": "0. Auth",
            "item": [
